TRACMASS
A Lagrangian trajectory code for oceanic and atmospheric general circulation models

The latest version of the TRACMASS code can be downloaded from

git clone https://github.com/TRACMASS/tracmass.git


  • TRACMASS computes particle trajectories from given velocity fields from both atmospheric and oceanic circulation models

  • TRACMASS trajectories can be set to advect 1) passivly with the 3D currents/winds, 2) set a fixed depth, 3) to have an addition vertical velocity for sedimentation studies, 4)  any specified depth function for bio-geo-chemical substances such as carbon, larvae, oil spill, radionucleids, etc.

  • TRACMASS integrates trajectories off-line, i.e. after the GCM has been integrated and the velocity fields have been stored. This makes it possible to calculate many more trajectories than would be possible on-line (simultaneously as the the GCM is integrated)

  • TRACMASS is set up to run with velocities integrated with models such as NEMO, ORCA, ROMS, POM, MICOM, IFS-ECMWF and EC-Earth

  • TRACMASS is based on Vries and Döös (2011) with the most recent version described in Döös et al. (2011)

  • TRACMASS makes it possible to estimate water paths, Lagrangian stream functions (barotropic and overturning), exchange times, particle sedimentation, etc

  • TRACMASS is written in FORTRAN 90 with modules and runs on UNIX platforms such as MAC OS X and Linux

The code is open source and you are free to download it. Implementation of the code requires good knowledge in

  • Geophysical fluid dynamics with its equations of motion

  • Finite differencing of these equations

  • Fortran

  • Unix
